---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Brad Cooke"
  description="Linux infrastructure, automation, Infrastructure-as-Code, and AI-assisted development."
>
  <section>
    <h1>Brad Cooke</h1>

    <p>
      Linux • Automation • Infrastructure as Code • AI
    </p>

    <p>
      I build Linux infrastructure, automation, and AI-assisted development
      environments while documenting what I learn along the way.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="/about/">About</a> ·
      <a href="/projects/">Projects</a> ·
      <a href="/contact/">Contact</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="featured-project">
    <p class="section-label">Featured Project</p>

    <h2>
      <a href="/projects/abbey-root/">Abbey Root</a>
    </h2>

    <p>
      A home Linux lab focused on Proxmox, Docker, Ansible,
      Infrastructure-as-Code, and AI-assisted development.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="/projects/abbey-root/">View project →</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Current Focus</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>Building BradCooke.com as a technical portfolio and project journal.</li>
      <li>Expanding Abbey Root as a reproducible Linux lab.</li>
      <li>Using Ansible, Git, templates, and generated documentation to reduce manual work.</li>
      <li>Developing ai-worker01 into a dedicated AI experimentation node.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What I’m Working Toward</h2>

    <p>
      My goal is to build useful systems, break them safely, understand how they
      work, automate what repeats, and share the lessons through this site.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .featured-project {
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-top: 0;
  }
</style>
